{"word":"H6140 - עָקַשׁ - ʻâqash - aw-kash' - Make crooked","slug":"H6140","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָקַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻâqash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-kash'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Make crooked"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05E7;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;qash</b> - <i>aw-kash'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>knot</i> or <i>distort</i>; figuratively to <i>pervert</i> (act or declare perverse): - make crooked, (prove, that is) perverse (-rt)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4625\">H4625</a>, <a href=\"#/H6141\">H6141</a>, <a href=\"#/H6142\">H6142</a>, <a href=\"#/H6143\">H6143</a>, <a href=\"#/H6144\">H6144</a>, <a href=\"#/H6145\">H6145</a>"}]}